(49, 1, '2010-05-19 17:40:43', '2010-05-19 17:40:43', 'Facts:\r\nUniploar Disorder, or Depression affects 17 million Americans.\r\n\r\nEncouraging News:\r\nDepression is treatable in 90% of all reported cases.\r\n\r\nUnipolar Disorder is described as major depression leading to:\r\n• Inability to focus on reading, work, TV\r\n• Reduced joy and pleasure in life\r\n• Lack of emotion\r\n• Physical ailments like many colds, or those without organic cause\r\n• Fatigue\r\n• Changes in appetite\r\n• Sleep pattern variations\r\n• Thinking and memory impairment\r\n• Sense of doom and disaster', 'Unipolar Disorder', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '32-revision-3', '', '', '2010-05-19 17:40:43', '2010-05-19 17:40:43', '', 32, 'http://www.dbsa-metrodetroit.org/wordpress/?p=49', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
